## Command Reference

### Complete Workflow Commands

**1. Check Git Repository:**
```bash
git rev-parse --git-dir > /dev/null 2>&1 && echo "Git repo exists" || echo "Not a git repo"
```

**2. Get Changed Files:**
```bash
# Simple list
git status --porcelain | awk '{print $2}'

# With proper parsing (handles renames)
git status --porcelain | while IFS= read -r line; do
    if [[ $line =~ ^R ]]; then
        echo "${line#*-> }"
    elif [[ $line =~ ^\?\? ]]; then
        echo "${line#?? }"
    else
        echo "${line#* }"
    fi
done
```

**3. Read Task from tasks.json:**
```bash
# Extract task data using jq (if available)
task_id="37"
jq -r ".master.tasks[] | select(.id == \"$task_id\") | {id, title, description}" .taskmaster/tasks/tasks.json
```

**4. Generate and Execute Commit:**
```bash
# Stage all changes
git add .

# Check if there are staged changes
if ! git diff --cached --quiet; then
    # Create commit with message file
    git commit -F commit_message.txt --no-verify
fi
```

## Integration

This rule is automatically applied after `set_task_status` when status is "done". No manual intervention required.

